Implemented the minimal fix in `lib/compress/zstd_compress.c`.

Changes:
- Caps row-based matchfinder `hashLog` to `28` bits.
- Extends short-cache CDict cParam adjustment to cap `chainLog` the same way `hashLog` was capped (`32 - ZSTD_SHORT_CACHE_TAG_BITS`, i.e. 24 bits).

Verification:
- Built successfully with debug assertions enabled:
  - `make -j2 zstd DEBUGLEVEL=2`
- Confirmed the reported style of repro no longer asserts/hangs on bounded input:
  - `head -c 1048576 /dev/zero | ./zstd -q -o /dev/null -7 --zstd=hlog=29`
